The best professor ever. Sam is always here to help students. you can learn a lot from this prof.

He simplified the exam by decomposing large questions so we were awarded for the parts we understood, and he kept in mind the students who hadn't taken a year 2 calc course in way he taught overlapping mtrial. The lectures were pushed from 3 to 2 hrs/wk bc we were trying in-class worksheets, this will improve w feedback from the survey he sent out.

He is a good prof, he knows a lot about stas and math, but he is not a good teacher because he cannot teach student efficiently. Especially there are lots of students, it feels like he cannot control his class very well, so I would suggest read and study yourself after his class, and ask him questions in his office hours, you will get much more.

rComments: Its his midterm/final. This prof thinks its best to put incredibly ambiguous word questions that none of his students have ever seen before on his tests. The midterm average for his stats course was a 37. After being bombarded with criticism, he still stands by his examination style and wants to do the same for the final. Expect to drop the course.

Definitely committed to students, he teaches around 6 courses through the year. If you are interested in quantitative finance, he is the only professor at UTSC who can provide you any insight seeing as he basically designed the department and runs its single handedly.  His organization with courses are perfect.
